  "text": "EMFs are a form of non-ionising radiation and as such are not sufficiently energetic to cause the type of tissue damage caused by x rays, for example. Unlike exposure to chemicals, once exposure to EMF ceases so does the direct influence in tissue. Moreover, there is little evidence for a build up of influence of low exposures over time. For example, the occurrence of cataracts has been linked to RF overexposure but there is no evidence that cataracts would arise from long term exposure to moderate RF levels. [CITATION_1] ",
